  "instructions": [
    "Heat the sesame oil in a kadhai vessel over medium high heat.",
    "Add the pork belly and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the sriracha, gochujang, soy sauce, and brown sugar, and stir to combine.",
    "Add the chopped green onions, tofu, and kimchi, and stir to combine.",
    "Reduce heat to medium low and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes, or until the pork is tender.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional green onions and kimchi if desired."
